-- China to Maintain Policy Stability, Continuity in Second Half, Wen Says
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-16T03:52:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-16/premier-wen-pledges-china-will-maintain-policy-stability-in-second-half.html

          
          
             China will maintain stability in its
economic policies in the second half of the year, Premier Wen
Jiabao said in a speech in Beijing today.  
 Wen reiterated the government’s goal of balancing
inflation, growth and the restructuring of the economy in a
speech at the Great Hall of the People. He also reaffirmed the
government’s commitment to maintain a pro-active fiscal policy
and moderately loose monetary policy.  
          
          


  


        